(18, 'What Is The Consistency Requirement on Instant Funding Plus Account?', '{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "There’s a consistency rule for Instant Funding Accounts", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Why this Rule?", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 1, "version": 1}, {"type": "linebreak", "version": 1}, {"mode": "normal", "text": "Funded Trader Markets’ Consistency Rule promotes steady profit growth and helps traders avoid emotional trading", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Important Details About the Consistency Rule For Instant Funding Accounts", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 1, "version": 1}, {"type": "linebreak", "version": 1}, {"mode": "normal", "text": "In an Instant Funding Account, you should not have made more than 20% of the total profit in one day.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "If a single day’s profit is more than 20% of your total profit in the Instant Funding Account, you will have to continue trading until there isn’t a day with more than 20%.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Calculation", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 1, "version": 1}, {"type": "linebreak", "version": 1}, {"mode": "normal", "text": "[Best Day % of Total Profit] = [Best Day Profit] ÷ [Overall Profit] * 100", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Best Day Profit means the highest single day profit.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}, {"type": "linebreak", "version": 1}, {"mode": "normal", "text": "Single Day’s Profit = Balance at 5pm est Today – Balance at 5pm est Yesterday", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Example (Instant Funding Account)", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 1, "version": 1}, {"type": "linebreak", "version": 1}, {"mode": "normal", "text": "If you made a total profit of $10,000 on an Instant Funding Account,", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}, {"type": "linebreak", "version": 1}, {"mode": "normal", "text": "To be eligible for withdrawal, there should not have been a single day with more than 20% of $10,000 (= $2,000). If there is a single day with more than 20% of total profit, then you have to keep on trading until the best day profit is less than 20% of the total profit.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": null}}', 'what-is-the-consistency-requirement-on-instant-funding-plus-account', 11, 5, 't', 'f', 'What Is The Consistency Requirement on Instant Funding Plus Account?', 'There’s a consistency rule for Instant Funding Accounts Why this Rule?Funded Trader Markets’ Consistency Rule promotes steady profit growth and helps tr...', '2025-09-22 11:39:52.335+00', '2025-09-22 11:39:52.334+00'),
